emcees.name: smugglaz
emcees.title: Emcee: Smugglaz | FlipTop Battle League
emcees.description: Smugglaz is already a renowned rapper even before the birth of FlipTop. So when the league was finally established, he instantly became part of the official roster. He made his debut at Down N South in 2010, where he displayed both his rapid fire flow and intricate rhyming style. Some may say that he only says random words in his lines, but he proved them all wrong when he faced Rapido at Bwelta Balentong 3. The Tondo emcee exposed all of his opponent’s weaknesses without straying from his trademark style. Many fans called it the biggest bodybag of 2016.

emcees.name: sur-henyo
emcees.title: Emcee: Sur Henyo | FlipTop Battle League
emcees.reppin: Pamilyari Ent, PKC, Rep The Hood Ent, Mensaheros, Hukbong Lirikal
emcees.description: Sur Henyo was part of the 2015 Process of Illumination in Central Luzon and his impressive showing was enough to get him a spot in FlipTop. He lost his first two battles, but was able to bounce back at the 2017 Isabuhay tournament. His improved pen game and delivery led him to the finals against crowd-favorite Mhot. Despite losing the aforementioned battle, he still managed to get the respect of battle rap fans and fellow emcees. Now, Sur Henyo is well-known not only for his technical bars and confidence but also for his clever angles.
